Azure VNets can connect to on-premise networks using VPN Gateway or ExpressRoute.

This enables hybrid cloud scenarios where resources are distributed across cloud and on-premise environments.

For example, an organization can connect its office network to Azure to access cloud-hosted applications.

A real-life use case is extending enterprise infrastructure to the cloud.

Another example is backup and disaster recovery where data is replicated between on-premise and Azure.

This connectivity allows seamless integration between environments.
